<p>The <b>European serin</b>, or just <b>serin</b>, (<i>Serinus serinus</i>) is the smallest European species of the family of <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Finch" title="Finch">finches</a> (Fringillidae) and is closely related to the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Atlantic_canary" title="Atlantic canary">canary</a>. Its diet consists mainly of a combination of <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bud" title="Bud">buds</a> and <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Seed" title="Seed">seeds</a>.</p>
<p></p>
